# Nested Drawer (Mobile)

On mobile (`max-md`), any drawer/sheet that opens **another** picker, menu, dropdown, or sub-screen must use **nested `@/components/ui/drawer`**, not inline panel swaps or overlapping dialogs.

## When to use

- Settings sub-panels (Appearance, Categories, …)
- Forms opened from inside a drawer (e.g. category edit with icon/color pickers)
- Any `Select` / `Popover` / secondary flow inside a bottom sheet

## Pattern

Nest `<Drawer>` inside the parent `<DrawerContent>`. Same `swipeDirection` as parent (usually `"down"` on mobile).

```tsx
<Drawer showSwipeHandle swipeDirection="down">
  <DrawerContent>{/* parent */}</DrawerContent>
  <Drawer showSwipeHandle swipeDirection="down">
    <DrawerTrigger render={<RowButton />} />
    <DrawerContent className={NESTED_DRAWER_SURFACE}>
      <DrawerTitle className="sr-only">Sub panel</DrawerTitle>
      <DrawerClose render={<BackButton />} />
      {children}
    </DrawerContent>
  </Drawer>
</Drawer>
```

## Helpers

- Generic shell: `@/components/shared/nested-drawer`
- Settings sub-panels: `@/components/settings/settings-nested-drawer`
- Forms inside a drawer: `@/components/shared/form-nested-drawer`
- Generic option lists: `@/components/shared/form-option-picker`
- Wallet lists: `@/components/journal/journal-wallet-picker`

## Do not

- Swap parent drawer body with `useState("panel")` on mobile — use nested drawer instead
- Close parent drawer and open a separate root drawer for a sub-flow (breaks native stack)
- Use `ResponsiveDialog` / root `Drawer` for sub-steps when already inside a drawer — nest another drawer

## Desktop

Desktop may keep inline navigation inside `Sheet` (settings) or `Dialog`. Nested drawer rule applies to **mobile only**.
